          "type": "text",
          "text": "Perfect! ✅ Circuit built successfully. Here's your wiring table and power summary:\n\n## Wiring Table\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Pin Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| D2 | Display → Segment A | (through R_A 220Ω) |\n| D3 | Display → Segment B | (through R_B 220Ω) |\n| D4 | Display → Segment C | (through R_C 220Ω) |\n| D5 | Display → Segment D | (through R_D 220Ω) |\n| D6 | Display → Segment E | (through R_E 220Ω) |\n| D7 | Display → Segment F | (through R_F 220Ω) |\n| D8 | Display → Segment G | (through R_G 220Ω) |\n| D9 | Add Button (pin A) | Signal input |\n| D10 | Subtract Button (pin A) | Signal input |\n| GND | Display (common) + both buttons (pin B) | Ground |\n\n## How It Works\n\n- **Display**: 7-segment LED with 7 series 220Ω resistors (one per segment) protects the Arduino pins.\n- **Buttons**: Wired active-LOW with INPUT_PULLUP. Pressing the button pulls the signal to GND.\n- **Logic**: Counter ranges 0–9. Add button increments (max 9), subtract button decrements (min 0). At limits, pressing does nothing.\n- **Debounce**: 50ms delay prevents rapid re-triggers.\n\n## Power Budget\n\n- **Per-pin load**: Each segment draws ~20mA @ 220Ω (5V – ~1.7V drop) ≈ 15mA per pin. All 7 segments lit = ~105mA total (well within 40mA rail headroom).\n- **Total board draw**: ~120mA (7 segments + buttons + Arduino overhead) — **safe** (Uno can source 200mA+).\n- **Status**: ✅ All pins and rails within safe limits."
        }
